3. 養聲
廣東話：歌手開演唱會之前，一定要好好養聲，否則聲帶勞損就麻煩啦。
English: Before a singer performs at a concert, they must take good care of their voice, otherwise vocal strain will be troublesome.

4. 票尾
廣東話：張飛嘅票尾撕落嚟，就係做收據用嘅。
English: The stub torn off the ticket serves as a receipt.

5. hacker
廣東話：個 hacker 入侵咗公司嘅電腦系統，搵咗好多私隱資料。
English: The hacker breached the company's computer system and found a lot of private data.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：園藝師種咗一株石斛蘭，佢依附喺樹上面生長，好特別。
English: The gardener planted an orchid (Dendrobium), which grows attached to a tree, very unique.

7. 吊詭 (矛盾、悖論)
廣東話：佢話自己唔信神，但又日日去教堂祈禱，真係好吊詭。
English: He says he doesn't believe in God, yet he goes to church to pray every day; it's truly contradictory.

8. 吊詭 (似非而是、荒謬)
廣東話：呢個方案好吊詭，明明係好主意，點解大家又覺得荒謬呢？
English: This proposal is quite absurd; it's obviously a good idea, so why do people find it ridiculous?

9. 各為其主
廣東話：兩間公司合作失敗，原來係因為佢哋各為其主，根本唔肯互相讓步。
English: The cooperation between the two companies failed because they were each acting in their own best interests and refused to compromise.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：古時嘅戰車上面都有軨蓋，可以遮風擋雨。
English: Ancient war chariots had a canopy (fengai) to shield against wind and rain.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：阿爸每星期日都會去球場打哥夫，好享受。
English: Dad goes to the golf course to play golf every Sunday; he really enjoys it.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間餐廳嘅甜品係免揀嘅，客人收到嘅就係固定嘅。
English: The desserts in this restaurant are non-selectable; customers receive a fixed set.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢成日喺人面前擺闊佬，其實佢根本冇咁多錢。
English: He always shows off his wealth in front of others, but he actually doesn't have that much money.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我細個好鍾意聽廣播劇，特別係夜晚嗰陣。
English: I loved listening to radio dramas when I was young, especially at night.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：舊屋入面嗰部錄影機好古老，但仲可以運作。
English: The video recorder in the old house is very old but still works.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：佢偷咗公司嘅錢，證據確鑿，真係吟詩吟唔甩。
English: He stole money from the company; the evidence is conclusive, and he has no way to deny it.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：教會下個月會舉辦佈道大會，邀請好多牧師嚟講道。
English: The church will hold a evangelism meeting next month, inviting many pastors to preach.

18. 寫手
廣東話：呢本書嘅內容係由一位專業寫手代筆嘅。
English: The content of this book was written by a professional ghostwriter.

19. 寫手 (代替他人寫作)
廣東話：佢請咗個寫手幫佢寫小說，因為佢自己寫唔出嚟。
English: He hired a ghostwriter to write the novel for him because he couldn't write it himself.

20. 代打
廣東話：個遊戲好難，我請人代打幫我過關。
English: The game is very hard, so I asked someone to play for me to get past the level.

21. 茶碗
廣東話：日本茶道入面，茶碗係一個好重要嘅道具。
English: In Japanese tea ceremony, the tea bowl is a very important utensil.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：斟茶嗰陣，用個茶隔可以將茶葉同茶湯分開，飲落去更香滑。
English: When pouring tea, using a tea strainer separates the leaves from the liquid, making it smoother to drink.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：老闆話員工唔可以遲到，但佢自己成日都遲到，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The boss says employees can't be late, but he is always late himself; it's truly a case of "only the magistrate is allowed to set fire, not the common people to light a lamp."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：今晚嘅音樂會，佢會表演一首獨唱。
English: At tonight's concert, he will perform a solo song.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢係個快人快事，有咗問題即刻解決，唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He is a straightforward person who deals with problems quickly and doesn't drag things out.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：呢個笑話好低俗，講緊廁所入面嘅四腳獸。
English: This joke is very vulgar; it talks about "four-legged beasts" in the toilet.

27. 無米粥
廣東話：我哋先煲無米粥，等雙方再諗清楚細節先至正式簽約。
English: We'll just have preliminary talks (like boiling porridge without rice) until both sides clarify the details before signing the contract.

28. 義會
廣東話：舊社會嘅窮人會組義會，大家輪流借錢用。
English: In the old society, poor people would form a rotating savings and credit association (yiui) to borrow money from each other in turns.

29. 榜文
廣東話：官府貼咗一張榜文，通告居民注意防火。
English: The government posted a notice on the bulletin board warning residents to be careful with fire.

30. MK 名
廣東話：個網民用咗一個好奇怪嘅 MK 名，好多人都唔識係咩意思。
English: The netizen used a very strange MK name, and many people don't know what it means. [end of text]


